Class Apartment

java.lang.Object
mainClasses.User
mainClasses.Apartment
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparator
public class Apartment extends User
The Apartment class is a subclass of User and it represents an apartment in a housing association. It contains various fields related to the apartment, such as its number, id, association id, number of people, area, central heating availability, gas contor availability, cold water contor old value, hot water contor old value, overdue amount, cold water contor new value, hot water contor new value, contor update date, individual water contors availability, old and new values for the conversion factors for cold and hot water contors, payment status, etc.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Ciprian Banci

    • Apartment

      public Apartment(String name, String email, String password, String phoneNo, Date registerDate, int no, int id, int association_id, int peopleNo, Double area, boolean centralHeating, boolean gasContor, Double cWContorOld, Double wWContorOld, Double overdue, Double cWContorNew, Double wWContorNew, Date contorUpdateDate, boolean individualWContors, Double cWCOldK, Double wWCOldK, Double cWNewK, Double wWNewK, boolean payedStatus)
      Constructs an Apartment object with the specified parameters.
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the user
      email - the email of the user
      password - the password of the user
      phoneNo - the phone number of the user
      registerDate - the registration date of the user
      no - the number of the apartment
      id - the ID of the apartment
      association_id - the ID of the association that the apartment belongs to
      peopleNo - the number of people living in the apartment
      area - the area of the apartment
      centralHeating - whether the apartment has central heating or not
      gasContor - whether the apartment has a gas contor or not
      cWContorOld - the old value of the cold water contor
      wWContorOld - the old value of the warm water contor
      overdue - the overdue debt for the apartment
      cWContorNew - the new value of the cold water contor
      wWContorNew - the new value of the warm water contor
      contorUpdateDate - the date when the contors were updated
      individualWContors - whether the apartment has individual warm water contors or not
      cWCOldK - the old value of the cold water coefficient
      wWCOldK - the old value of the warm water coefficient
      cWNewK - the new value of the cold water coefficient
      wWNewK - the new value of the warm water coefficient
      payedStatus - whether the apartment has paid its debts or not
